<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 2:51PM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southern Kalamazoo
County through 415 PM EDT...
At 249 PM EDT, trained weather spotters reported a strong
thunderstorm over Portage, moving southeast at 10 mph. Another
thunderstorm is developing near Scotts which may contain small hail.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Trained weather spotters reported pea sized hail just south
of Portage .
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Portage...             Vicksburg...
Schoolcraft...         Kalamazoo-Battle Cre...
Fulton...
Scotts...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
